cs.GR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG. 

The paper presents a system for generating 3D scenes using natural language input, which involves techniques from natural language processing (NLP), computer vision (CV), and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.GR (Graphics) is the most likely category as it deals with 3D graphics and visualization. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper involves NLP techniques for processing natural language input. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper involves ML techniques for inferring an arrangement of objects in the scene. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also possible as the paper involves CV techniques for extracting constraints from the input text. Finally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves ML techniques for learning a spatial knowledge base from an existing database of 3D scenes and object models.
